# Hardware Architecture (Preliminary)

## 1. Pin Mapping (Raspberry Pi 4)
| Component | GPIO Pin | Protocol | Purpose |
| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **PN532 RFID** | 9, 10, 11 | SPI | Fast pet identification |
| **NEMA 17** | 17, 27 | Digital | Precision food dispensing |
| **Solenoid Lock** | 18 | PWM/Dig | Door locking mechanism |
| **JSN-SR04T** | 23, 24 | Digital | Ultrasonic food level sensing |
| **Dual OLEDs** | 2, 3 | I2C | Real-time UI feedback |
| **E-Button** | 22 | Interrupt | Emergency manual override |

## 2. Power Distribution
- **12V DC Adapter:** Powers the NEMA 17 motor and Solenoid Lock via Relay.
- **5V Buck Converter:** Steps down 12V to 5V to power the Raspberry Pi 4 and sensors.
- **UPS Shield:** Provides battery backup to prevent system failure during power outages.
